	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=124650><span id=Scholar>Guyon</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>28 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.43]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>&lt;THIS IS NOT MEANT AS A FLAME TO ANYONE OR ANYTHING IT IS MY ATTEMPT TO GAIN A BETTER PERSPECTIVE ON WHAT A WARRIOR IS AND A VENTING OF THE PROBLEM I HAVE WITH THIS FORUM IN PARTICULAR DISCUSS INTELLIGENTLY IF YOU LIKE PLEASE&gt;<br><br>Well now thats out of the way down to it. First Strategy: <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;   Ive heard of people saying that the good warriors know that there is more toa warrior then occasionally hitting taunt and kick for 3 minutes.<br>Well Ive never seen anyone post in this forum what else there is?! Its nice that you all hate that the casters dont view you as anything but a meatshield but until you start telling everyone else what youve discovered in your fights thats all we will be!<br>      Now here is what ive learned 1. save taunt for when its needed and hit it right after the wiz or cleric lets loose the uber nuke, unless of course you are trying to grab agro off someone in which case slamming that key seems to work. 2. I havent used kick in ages! Im a large race and can slam so i use that. It seems that bash would be a better designed skill since it has limitations built into it (IE: holding a shield and no dualweild) Bash/slam can stun and it interrupts casters. Also it seems the AI notices if you use slam to interrupt spells and will wait for you to slam before using the spell. hold off on slamming and the mob wont cast on you, this may seem odd and i may be wrong but if you look you may see what i mean when fighting shaman type enemies.<br><br>Well thats all the strategy ive found so far and it works pretty well for me.<br><br>Now on to the forum here. <br>    Where do you get those wonderful toys?<br>         well mr 25 warrior you should go and get 1-3k plat and blow it all on a single weapon. TWO PROBLEMS 1. where the heck does a 25 warrior get 1k plat to blow on ONE item! I hang around the spires in SK and go in paw when i can and lets be honest im not making 1k in there 2. you have to find people who will sell the item! I dont know about you but i play on the firionia vie server and to be honest compared to the economies that you all describe FV's is nonexistant. So even saving up the money is useless if nobody is selling the item. We are not all twinks especially on the FV server where twinking is almost as nonexistant as the economy. So next time someone asks you if they should upgrade their centi longsword or wurmy cause they hit level 12 think about what they just said for a second.<br>Whooo im exahusted from this ranting. well thats all i have to say for now. Maybe this will help those who really need the help and inspire you all to think about what you say here. <br>&lt;I REPEAT THIS WASNT MEANT AS AN INSULT TO ANYONE&gt;<br></p>&nbsp;<br>Gatsu<br>28th season warrior<br>Firionia vie<br>"I am not a twink try and keep that in mind"</td></td></tr>
