	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=103498><span id=Sage>kdsktan</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>129 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>as a warrior you must have really good situational awareness. you have to dictate when to off-tank, who off-tanks, watch out to pull aggros of casters and clerics. always taunt mezzed mobs before breaking. also, when casters are using pets, make sure you turn the mob so that the back faces the pets. lets face it, pets are not very clever. in a bad pull situation, as you normally have highest hp, try and buy some time for others to run off before you do. <br>also, weapons - you should try and have a mix of stuff - low delay, high dmg, etc. also a decent 2hs - when you are figting a mob with a DS, switch to 2hs to save yourself getting hit lots. <br>if you want to know more about warriors theres a decent post in everlore.com under class strategy guide.<br>also, in raids if you are MA then u must control the casters and other melee. i.e. you tell them when to come in etc and only after you have established aggro. have lots of hot keys. i have keys for my discs, to tell people i am taunting, to tell people to back off the mob etc, to ask for heals, buffs, haste etc. <br>at the end of the day, warriors are never going to be as complex in their use as say an ench or a cleric, but its more than hack and kick.<br><br><br><br> <br><br> <br><br><br> <br><br><br><br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
