	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61851><span id=Scholar>Vykore</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>179 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.23]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I'm wondering, how succesful is smithing on FV? I mean do a lot of people buy banded? If so it may be a good source of income for yourself, not to mention one day you could make fine plate.<br><br>For earrings you could start going with friends to iceclad to hunt cougars. Once in a while they'll drop cougar claws. Though they are rare drops it may be worth a shot.<br><br>You may want to check up the level for this but if you get a group of friends (Hopefully one of them can cast Inv vs. Undead) and head to the basement in Unrest you can go through the secret door and pull the mobs into the hallway. There's a ghost of a dwarf in there who drops the Jagged Bands. Seems to drop everytime from him. Good upgrade for your rings. These rings go super cheap on my server. Usually only 25pp a pop.<br><br>In runnyeye Lord Picklaw (35th level boss) can spawn anywhere on the bottom floor. He can drop a few different goodies. A head piece that has 6ac, 6str and +6 to all saves, and a Grotseque Alloy Mask which is 6ac, +7 dex and some other stats too, I think to Agility and svm. (-15 cha, but who cares right? lol) He almost always has either the Black Alloy Longsword or Bastard sword but any mob can carry one on the bottom level. The Longsword would be a great upgrade from your Langseax. Lots of Black Alloy armour drops in Runnyeye and can prob be used to sell or barter on your server. Not to mention the Goblins drop good coin. ;)<br><br>In Stonebrunt the Kobolds can drop Etched Iron armour. This armour usually has a bonus to svm and the AC is one higher than bronze (one lower than Fine Plate) I didn't do much hunting there but when the zone first went live My friends got me the Breastplate which lasted me a while. They drop all kinds of armour for different slots but it's not too common. Still it might be a great place for XP, though I don't know if it's a place to go and find a group. If you bring friends there's plenty to hunt though. Also in Stonebrunt in the kittie village, there's a little girl who said she lost her dice. The dice are on Prince Ragnor in the Warrens. Easily soloable at your level and when you turn in the dice she gives you a Ball of Yarn which as 4 charges of root. (Not bad to carry around) Also the prince drops a semi decent plate bracer. Think it may be better than bronze but has +3 wisdom to it. You can use that to barter with clerics or paladins to if you want.<br><br>You didn't list what was in your hands. But if you don't have crafted and you're still fighting in SK, keep an eye open for the aviak darter for the piece for Crafted Gauntlets. ;)<br><br>Good Luck!<br><br> <br><br><br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Apr 10 16:38:58 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br>Zaviax McCleo <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=235432" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=235432</a><br><br>Shadow of the Dragon<br>Tunare<br>(www.eqsod.com)</td></td></tr>
